OL,4,CMineworkers' Pension Scheme: Rejection
OL,5,Ca 'slap in the face'
OL,6, Calls for the government to give #1.2bn
OL,7, of pension funds to ex-miners have been
OL,8, rejected, in what has been described as
OL,9, a "slap in the face".
OL,11,FCurrently the government gets half of
OL,12,Fany surplus from the miners' scheme, a
OL,13,Fdeal that has made it #4.4bn so far.
OL,15,FIn April, a parliamentary committee
OL,16,Fcalled for a review of the arrangement
OL,17,Fbut the government has said it believed
OL,18,Fthe scheme was "fair and beneficial".
OL,20,FA former Nottinghamshire miner said he
OL,21,Fwas "devastated" by the decision.
